Addressing this problem is crucial for protecting the commercial value of original artists and maintaining the integrity of the music industry. Accurate detection methods can also prevent the spread of unauthorized reproductions, ensuring fair compensation and recognition for artists. Additionally, this research can contribute to broader applications in audio analysis and machine learning.

**[Question 3] - Why is it hard?**
Developing advanced augmentation techniques that preserve musical nuances is challenging due to the complexity of human voice characteristics. Additionally, creating a robust detection model that can withstand adversarial attacks requires sophisticated algorithms and extensive testing. Ensuring scalability and efficiency for real-time applications adds another layer of complexity.

**[Question 4] - Why hasn't it been solved before?**
Previous research has focused on basic augmentation techniques and detection models, but there is a lack of advanced methods that address the specific challenges of singing voice deepfake detection. The complexity of human voice characteristics and the need for robustness against adversarial attacks have not been fully addressed. Additionally, integrating advanced machine learning techniques and ensuring scalability have been underexplored.

