**Summary:** This paper presents an enhanced framework for singing voice deepfake detection (SVDD) by improving the SingGraph detection framework. We address the challenges of high detection accuracy, computational efficiency, and generalization across different genres and styles. Our approach includes the development of advanced augmentation techniques to simulate real-world conditions, optimization of the graph-based back-end model, and the use of transfer learning and multi-task learning to improve generalization. We also develop a real-time version of the SingGraph model to enable practical applications. Our results demonstrate significant improvements in detection accuracy, reduced computational complexity, and enhanced generalization capabilities, making the framework suitable for real-world deployment in the music industry and beyond.

---

This abstract provides a concise overview of the research, methodology, key findings, and implications. It sets the stage for the detailed sections that will follow in the research paper.

Would you like to proceed with drafting the next section, the **Introduction**, or is there any specific part of the abstract you would like to refine further?

