umentation:** Provide comprehensive documentation of the system, including setup instructions and usage guidelines.\n\n### Deliverables\n- **Implemented System:** A fully functional system for detecting synthetic singing voices.\n- **Experiment Results:** Detailed reports on the performance of the system.\n- **Documentation:** Comprehensive documentation of the system and experiments.\n\n### Timeline\n- **Week 1-2:** Setup development environment and develop advanced feature extraction techniques.\n- **Week 3-4:** Integrate different models and optimize for scalability and real-time processing.\n- **Week 5-6:** Incorporate multimodal analysis and prepare datasets.\n- **Week 7-8:** Conduct experiments and evaluate the system.\n- **Week 9-10:** Document the system and prepare final reports.\n\nBy following this structured plan, you can ensure a systematic and thorough implementation of the proposed research idea.', 'agent6': 'Given the detailed research proposal, the next logical step is to **draft a comprehensive research paper** based on the refined research idea. This paper will serve as a formal document to present the research, methodology, results, and conclusions to the academic community. Here’s a structured approach to drafting the research paper:\n\n### Drafting the Research Paper\n\n#### 1. **Abstract**\n- **Summary:** Write a concise summary of the research, including the problem, methodology, key findings, and implications.\n\n#### 2. **Introduction**\n- **Background:** Provide an overview of the advancements in singing voice synthesis and the need for deepfake detection.\n- **Problem Statement:** Clearly state the problem being addressed.\n- **Objectives:** Outline the objectives of the research.\n- **Significance:** Discuss the importance of the research and its potential impact.\n\n#### 3. **Related Work**\n- **Literature Review:** Summarize existing research on singing voice deepfake detection, including the SingGraph framework.\n- **Gaps:** Identify 